# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Trapeza — P0 spike credentials. Copy to `.env` and fill in.
#   cp .env.example .env
# NEVER commit `.env`. It is gitignored. All values are TESTNET only.
# See SETUP.md for how to obtain each value and fund the wallets.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Shared / network ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Arc testnet RPC. Default is fine; override only if you run your own node.
ARC_RPC_URL=https://rpc.testnet.arc.network


# ── Spike 1: x402 / Gateway nanopayment  (packages/adapter-gateway) ──────────
# Buyer wallet: pays the nanopayment. MUST be funded on Arc testnet with BOTH
#   - native USDC (used for gas, 18 decimals), and
#   - ERC-20 USDC at 0x3600000000000000000000000000000000000000 (6 decimals).
# Generate a key with `cast wallet new` (Foundry) or any EVM keygen, then fund
# it from the Circle faucet (see SETUP.md). NO Circle API key is needed for this
# path — it is self-managed-wallet + the public x402 batching facilitator.
BUYER_PRIVATE_KEY=0xYOUR_FUNDED_BUYER_PRIVATE_KEY

# Seller wallet: receives the nanopayment. Address only (no key needed here).
SELLER_ADDRESS=0xYOUR_SELLER_ADDRESS

# Optional knobs:
# PRICE=$0.001
# DEPOSIT_AMOUNT=0.1


# ── Spike 2: ERC-8004 identity registration  (packages/adapter-arc) ──────────
# Owner wallet: registers the agent identity. MUST be funded with Arc-testnet
# native USDC for gas (~0.006 USDC/tx). Self-managed viem path → only this key
# is required.
OWNER_PRIVATE_KEY=0xYOUR_FUNDED_OWNER_PRIVATE_KEY

# Optional — if set, the spike ALSO records one ERC-8004 reputation event.
# Per ERC-8004 the owner cannot rate its own agent, so this MUST be a DIFFERENT
# funded wallet than OWNER_PRIVATE_KEY.
# VALIDATOR_PRIVATE_KEY=0xYOUR_FUNDED_VALIDATOR_PRIVATE_KEY

# Optional — agent metadata URI. Defaults to the Arc quickstart example IPFS URI.
# METADATA_URI=ipfs://bafkreibdi6623n3xpf7ymk62ckb4bo75o3qemwkpfvp5i25j66itxvsoei


# ── Alternative ERC-8004 path: Circle Developer-Controlled Wallets ───────────
# NOT used by the default spike (which uses the viem self-managed path above).
# Needed only if you switch the adapter to the Circle Wallets + Gas Station path
# (DESIGN.md §5, for the agent fleet). Obtain from https://console.circle.com.
# CIRCLE_API_KEY=
# CIRCLE_ENTITY_SECRET=
